Store Rasa Conversations in MySQL Database

Python 3.8.18
Rasa 3.6.17
pymysql 1.1.0

1. Create a MySQL connection. Create a database in it.

2. Set up SQL as Tracker store in the endpoints.yml file

3. Train your bot

In Your MySQL Database

- Check all conversations using

SELECT * from rasa.events WHERE type_name=’user’ ;

- Check unanswered queries using

SELECT data from rasa.events WHERE intent_name=’nlu_fallback’;

- Fetch JSON response from the column using

SELECT json_extract(data, ‘$.text’) AS Fallback FROM rasa.events WHERE intent_name=’nlu_fallback’;